UMC Makes Chips for Amazon’s Kindle Fire, Commercial Times Says

-- B y   C h i n m e i   S u n g
-- 
2011-10-23T22:40:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-23/umc-makes-chips-for-amazon-s-kindle-fire-commercial-times-says.html
United Microelectronics Corp. (2303)  is
sole manufacturer of the processor chips that power  Amazon.com
Inc. (AMZN) ’s Kindle Fire tablet computers, the Commercial Times
reported today, without saying where it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
